description:
## File
Modify: `flake.nix`

## Changes
Add `packages` output with `ansible-idempotency-test` wrapper. The flake already has ARA + websocket-client in the Python env, so we can wrap the script:

```nix
packages = forEachSupportedSystem ({ pkgs }:
  let
    pythonEnv = pkgs.python3.withPackages (ps: with ps; [
      ansible websocket-client ara  # existing deps
    ]);
  in {
    ansible-idempotency-test = pkgs.writeShellApplication {
      name = "ansible-idempotency-test";
      runtimeInputs = [ pythonEnv ];
      text = '
        exec python3 ${./scripts/ansible-idempotency-test} "$@"
      ';
    };
  });
```

## Result
This enables: `nix run github:claytono/infra#ansible-idempotency-test`

## Note
The existing flake already has the ARA package built as a custom buildPythonPackage (lines 45-78 in flake.nix). Reuse that Python environment.
